.

Théry et al. (2008)
interpreted the crepuscular flight activity of this species as a mechanism that improves visual communication among conspecifics. At mid-range (> 
0.5 m
) in the low-intensity dusk lighting, the dark blue, metallic (structural) body coloration is seen at higher contrast against ambient background and active individuals become more visible to each other; at shorter range (<
0.5 m
), enhancement of contrast between the black head horn and metallic pronotum probably functions in species recognition.
